==Family==
Dukakis is married to [[Kitty Dukakis|Katharine D. (Kitty) Dukakis]]. They have three children: John, Andrea, and Kara. During the second presidential debate on October 13, 1988, in Los Angeles, Dukakis revealed that he and his wife had had another child, who died about 20 minutes after birth. Dukakis is the cousin of actress [[Olympia Dukakis]].<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0241144/bio IMDb] — Biography for Michael Dukakis. Retrieved October 18, 2009.</ref>

The Dukakises continue to reside in the home that they bought in the early 1970s in [[Brookline, Massachusetts]], where they both grew up, but live in [[Los Angeles]] during the winter while he teaches at [[University of California, Los Angeles|UCLA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/ws/index.php?pid=17959 |title=George Bush: Appointment of Katharine D. Dukakis as a Member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council |publisher=Presidency.ucsb.edu |date= |accessdate=2015-04-05}}</ref>

